The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICL to hold tri-series from April 9
                                                   ICL to hold tri-series from April 9
                      
	 Mumbai: The rebel Indian Cricket League (ICL) will organise a triangular Twenty20 series with ICLs India, Pakistan and a World XI vying for the title in a tournament to be played from April 9 to 15.         
	Named ICL 20s World Series 2008, the tri-series, to be played at the Lal Bahadur Shastri Stadium in Hyderabad, will have seven matches with teams playing each other twice followed by the final.         
	All the matches will be broadcast live on TEN Sports and ZEE Sports from 7pm to 10pm. With ICL World Series 2008, our promising domestic boys will face the toughest challenge of proving their credentials against two of the mightiest teams in the world, ICL chairman and former India captain Kapil Dev said.         
	The final Indian squad will be selected after the Edelweiss 20s Challenges second semi-finals, he added. Inzaman-ul Haq will lead the ICL Pakistan team, while Chris Cairns will lead the international players representing ICL World XI.         
	Moin Khan will coach the Pakistan side while former England off-spinner John Emburey will coach the world team.         
	Steve Rixon, former Australian wicketkeeper, will coach the Indian team, while the captain will be selected later.         
	Incidentally, the Lal Bahadur Stadium would stage the second and third finals of the ongoing Edelweiss 20s Challenge on April 6 and 7.                 (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                   
